   Editorial Contact Information
   Letters to the Editor
   If you have a comment on a particular article that you would like considered for publication in Science News, e-mail it to editors@sciencenews.org or send it by post to:
   Editors
   Science News
   1719 N Street N.W.
   Washington, D.C. 20036-2801
   Please include your name, location and the name and date of the article you are writing about. Letters are subject to editing for clarity, grammar and space. Originals will not be returned.
   Freelance Article Submission
   Science News does not accept unsolicited queries or manuscripts. News and features are written entirely by staff writers or professional science journalists under contract for specific
   assignments. Freelance science journalists who wish to be considered for future assignments may send a resume and one writing sample in electronic form to freelance@sciencenews.org.
   News Releases
   News releases should be directed to individual reporters based on their areas of responsibility as indicated by news beat. All releases should be sent electronically to
   newsreleases@sciencenews.org and the name of the appropriate reporter included in the subject line. If no reporter seems obviously appropriate, the release may be sent to Attention: Editorial
   Assistant.
   Releases regarding an upcoming event or publication should be provided as far in advance as possible, ideally at least three weeks before the event or embargo time. Notices of meetings and
   conferences should be provided at least a year in advance when possible.
   In general, Science News does not cover new product announcements, financial results or promotions and other personnel matters.
   Contacting Science News Reporters and Editors
   To reach an individual reporter or editor by e-mail, please send a message to editors@sciencenews.org with the name of the individual in the subject line. The message will be forwarded to the
   individual.
   To telephone a reporter or editor, please call the Science News main number, (202) 785-2255, Monday-Friday between 9 a.m. and 5 p.m. EST. To send a fax to a reporter or editor, please use (202)
   659-0365.

